column5: Hey everyone  I know this is a fishing forum but has anyone hunted on grand river conservation's "miscellaneous hunting property"? There's a bunch around. I got my eye on one south of elora. Just wondering if it's worth paying their fees? PM me details if you like. It's not my intent to see anything get hunted out.  Thanks, JW
yes its worth paying the fees, good numbers of turkeys and deer in many of the tracts  Dan
